OL,7,FHis mobility and speech becomes
OL,8,Faffected when he has not taken his
OL,9,Fmedication.
OL,11,FHis mother said: "He made the tea and
OL,12,Fwe had normal conversation that night.
OL,13,FHe went to bed at around 11pm and then
OL,14,FI got up and checked him at 5.30am,
OL,15,Fbut he wasn't there and was not
OL,16,Fanswering his phone. I thought that
OL,17,Fmaybe he had just gone out for a walk."
OL,19,FHis family believe he used public
OL,20,Ftransport to travel because Andy is
OL,21,Funable to walk very far on foot.
